    "body": "Hello, I have a similar issue of wrong cursor placement within Windows \"Git Bash\" in Microsoft Terminal only (works well with `mintty` terminal from \"Git Bash\" package as far as I know).\nTypically, after `ctrl-s` or recall command from history, then using `ctrl-a` or `ctrl-e` leads to incorrect cursor placement.\nAs a work-around, a refresh with `ctrl-l` allows to reset cursor placement and observe how command has been mangled by previous keystrokes",
